## 🌊 TURSO INTEGRATION DETAILS

### **🔧 TECHNICAL IMPLEMENTATION**
```
📊 DatabaseBackend Enum: SQLite / Turso abstraction
🔧 DatabaseConfig: Environment-based configuration
🌊 TursoConfig: URL, auth token, database name
📜 Migration: ServiceManager backend switching methods
🚀 Setup Scripts: Automated Turso setup and configuration
🔄 Switch Scripts: Runtime backend switching utilities
📝 Documentation: Complete integration guides and examples
🔒 Security: Token-based authentication with environment variables
🌍 Global: Edge SQL with automatic replication
⚡ Performance: Optimized connection pooling and caching
```

### **📋 CONFIGURATION OPTIONS**
```
🌊 Environment Variables:
├── TURSO_URL: Database connection URL
├── TURSO_AUTH_TOKEN: Authentication token
├── TURSO_DATABASE_NAME: Database identifier
└── ENABLE_TURSO: Backend selection flag

📁 Configuration Files:
├── config/turso/turso.env: Environment configuration
├── config/turso/turso.env.example: Template file
└── config/turso/README.md: Setup documentation

🔧 Feature Flags:
├── turso: Enable Turso support (libsql dependency)
├── database: Enable database service
└── default: Includes database + surfpool features
```

### **🚀 USAGE EXAMPLES**
```
# Switch to Turso backend
./scripts/switch-db.sh turso

# Switch to SQLite backend
./scripts/switch-db.sh sqlite

# Check current backend
./scripts/switch-db.sh status

# Setup Turso from scratch
./scripts/setup-turso.sh

# Run with Turso
cargo run --features turso

# Run with SQLite (default)
cargo run
```

